TITLE: Importing Excalidraw in a Bundler Environment
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to import Excalidraw components, styles, and types when using a bundler like Vite or Next.js. Shows proper import syntax for the ESM format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/blob/master/packages/excalidraw/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// excalidraw library with public API
import * as excalidrawLib from "@excalidraw/excalidraw";
// excalidraw react component
import { Excalidraw } from "@excalidraw/excalidraw";
// excalidraw styles, usually auto-processed by the build tool (i.e. vite, next, etc.)
import "@excalidraw/excalidraw/index.css";
// excalidraw types (optional)
import type { ExcalidrawImperativeAPI } from "@excalidraw/excalidraw/types";
```

