TITLE: Implementing Custom Sidebar with Tabs in Excalidraw
DESCRIPTION: A complete example demonstrating how to implement a custom sidebar with multiple tabs in Excalidraw. The example shows how to create a dockable sidebar with two tabs, custom styling, and a toggle button in the footer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/blob/master/dev-docs/docs/@excalidraw/excalidraw/api/children-components/sidebar.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
function App() {
  const [docked, setDocked] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div style={{ height: "580px" }}>
      <Excalidraw
        UIOptions={{
          // this effectively makes the sidebar dockable on any screen size,
          // ignoring if it fits or not
          dockedSidebarBreakpoint: 0,
        }}
      >
        <Sidebar name="custom" docked={docked} onDock={setDocked}>
          <Sidebar.Header />
          <Sidebar.Tabs style={{ padding: "0.5rem" }}>
            <Sidebar.Tab tab="one">Tab one!</Sidebar.Tab>
            <Sidebar.Tab tab="two">Tab two!</Sidebar.Tab>
            <Sidebar.TabTriggers>
              <Sidebar.TabTrigger tab="one">One</Sidebar.TabTrigger>
              <Sidebar.TabTrigger tab="two">Two</Sidebar.TabTrigger>
            </Sidebar.TabTriggers>
          </Sidebar.Tabs>
        </Sidebar>

        <Footer>
          <Sidebar.Trigger
            name="custom"
            tab="one"
            style={{
              marginLeft: "0.5rem",
              background: "#70b1ec",
              color: "white",
            }}
          >
            Toggle Custom Sidebar
          </Sidebar.Trigger>
        </Footer>
      </Excalidraw>
    </div>
  );
}
```

