TITLE: HTML Setup for Browser Integration of Excalidraw
DESCRIPTION: HTML structure for directly integrating Excalidraw in a browser environment. Uses import maps to handle React dependencies and includes necessary stylesheet links and asset path configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/blob/master/dev-docs/docs/@excalidraw/excalidraw/integration.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Excalidraw in browser</title>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://esm.sh/@excalidraw/excalidraw@0.18.0/dist/dev/index.css"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./index.css" />
    <script>
    	window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH = "https://esm.sh/@excalidraw/excalidraw@0.18.0/dist/prod/";
		</script>
    <script type="importmap">
      {
        "imports": {
          "react": "https://esm.sh/react@19.0.0",
          "react/jsx-runtime": "https://esm.sh/react@19.0.0/jsx-runtime",
          "react-dom": "https://esm.sh/react-dom@19.0.0"
          }
      }
    </script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Excalidraw Embed Example</h1>
      <div id="app"></div>
    </div>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="packages/excalidraw/index.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

